-- Anglo Says The West Wall Copper Deposit in Chile Holds 750 Million Tons
-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 2010-10-19T06:05:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/anglo-xstrata-s-west-wall-copper-deposit-in-chile-holds-750-million-tons.html
Anglo American Plc said the West
Wall copper project in central Chile holds 750 million tons of
resources.  Anglo and Xstrata Plc each own 50 percent of the mining
company which operates the project.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
